quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  28,1,"Tâ-Sîn-Mîm"
  28,2,"These are the Verses of the manifest Book (that makes clear truth from falsehood, good from evil)."
  28,3,"We recite to you some of the news of Mûsâ (Moses) and Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) in truth, for a people who believe (in this Qur’ân, and in the Oneness of Allâh)."
  28,4,"Verily, Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) exalted himself in the land and made its people sects, weakening (oppressing) a group (i.e. Children of Israel) among them: killing their sons, and letting their females live. Verily, he was of the Mufsidûn(i.e. those who commit great sins and crimes, oppressors, tyrants)."
  28,5,"And We wished to do a favour to those who were weak (and oppressed) in the land, and to make them rulers and to make them the inheritors,"